&lt;p&gt;Anthropic’s mission is to create reliable, interpretable, and steerable AI systems. We want AI to be safe and beneficial for our users and for society as a whole. Our team is a quickly growing group of committed researchers, engineers, policy experts, and business leaders working together to build beneficial AI systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Events Lead, Enterprise&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Enterprise Events Lead at Anthropic, you will own the development and execution of enterprise-focused events that accelerate pipeline, deepen customer relationships, and elevate Anthropic&#39;s brand presence with key enterprise audiences. You will be responsible for designing and delivering high-impact event experiences—from major industry conferences to hosted summits, and partner activations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll collaborate closely with Sales, Partnerships, Product Marketing, and Creative teams to ensure every event touchpoint reinforces Anthropic&#39;s position as a leader in safe, frontier AI. You&#39;ll bring a strategic mindset grounded in data, a talent for flawless execution under pressure, and the ability to translate complex enterprise goals into compelling in-person and hybrid experiences. This is a high-visibility role with significant cross-functional impact, ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of strategy and logistics in a fast-moving environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development and execution of enterprise events, aligning programs to pipeline generation, account engagement, and brand objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a team of full time and contracted employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conceptualize and produce hosted events such as executive roundtables, customer summits, and intimate dinners that support account-based marketing goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales and Partnerships teams to optimize meeting programs, briefing schedules, and on-site engagement strategies at events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Creative Studio on experience design, ensuring Anthropic and Claude brands are represented consistently and compellingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage end-to-end event logistics including vendor relationships, budgets, contracts, staffing plans, and timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop pre-event and post-event communications, including &quot;Know Before You Go&quot; guides, staff and speaker training, and attendee follow-up plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and track event KPIs—including lead generation, pipeline influence, meeting volume, and attendee engagement—to measure ROI and inform future strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable event processes, playbooks, and documentation to support Anthropic&#39;s growing event portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationships with external event agencies, vendors, and venue partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel on-site to events to provide hands-on logistics management and ensure seamless execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement through post-event analysis and stakeholder feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You may be a good fit if you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have 15+ years of experience in enterprise event marketing, field marketing, or a related role, ideally at a high-growth B2B technology company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a proven track record of executing large-scale conferences, trade shows, and hosted executive events that drive measurable business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are highly organized with exceptional project management skills and the ability to manage multiple complex events simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience partnering with enterprise sales teams to align event programs with pipeline and revenue goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are a clear, effective communicator who can collaborate across functions—from Creative and Marketing to Sales and Executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong budget management experience, including vendor negotiation and contract management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are comfortable with data and analytics, using event metrics to optimize programs and demonstrate ROI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in fast-paced, ambiguous environments and can adapt quickly when priorities shift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are willing and excited to travel regularly (approximately 40% of the time) for on-site event execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a genuine interest in AI and care about ensuring that transformative AI systems are developed and deployed responsibly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong candidates may also:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience with event technology platforms (e.g., Splash, Cvent)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience building an enterprise events function or program from an early stage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring a strong network of event industry contacts, including venues, production agencies, and AV partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience with account-based marketing (ABM) strategies and how events fit within a broader demand generation ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
